				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Apple laptop refresh
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1768156">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I like being able to post to twitter and facebook directly from the notification center on my laptop that is built-in.  Also, OS X has a lot of well designed management of desktops and windows organization, but does not have a baked in way to manage frame sizes well, one area that is lacking.  There are non-baked in solutions though, still an area for improvement.  Storing user customizations for settings in iCloud sounds like something it is perfectly suited for.  Such behavior is popular among nerds who store dot files on github, but not something everyone else thinks to do.
						</blockquote>
