		</div>
	</div>
</div>Yeah, Apple uses their own file system inherited from Mac OS with some changes in OS X.  <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File_system#OS_X" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File_system#OS_X</a>  <br />
<br />
I don't think it's used anywhere else in computing.  Seems bizarre that it is nontrivial to use various filesystems on the proprietary operating systems when it is so trivial in bsd/linux.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
