				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Apple laptop refresh
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1769577">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							All of the success Apple has ever had comes from opening doors.  And their downfall every single time is closing them.<br />
<br />
When the iPod and iTunes worked fine with Windows, it became a huge selling point.  You had well developed hardware that worked with what everyone else was using.<br />
<br />
Since that first step, they've been methodically closing doors.  iTunes for windows is a huge, bloated piece of shit, if you have an iPhone, all of the &quot;cool&quot; features only work with other iPhone users and Mac, so less than 1/4 of the phones being sold today.  They make superior hardware/software combinations, but since you can't use them with anything that isn't overpriced, they're severely limited.
						</blockquote>
